(# Project Documentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Rural Mental Health Screening AI is a browser-based and backend-supported screening platform built for rural and resource-constrained mental health workflows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It combines:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- multilingual questionnaire intake,) Tj
T*
(- narrative text analysis,) Tj
T*
(- optional audio and image capture,) Tj
T*
(- passive biomarker support,) Tj
T*
(- adaptive screening,) Tj
T*
(- model statistics and quality checks,) Tj
T*
(- PDF reporting,) Tj
T*
(- record lookup and export,) Tj
T*
(- offline-first fallback support,) Tj
T*
(- a research-ready paper and evaluation toolkit.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project is designed so a health worker can complete a screening session in one flow, review the result immediately, save it to a local or backend store, and later reopen the record for reporting or analysis.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Project Goals) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system is built around these goals:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Support rural screening workflows with low friction.) Tj
T*
(2. Present the workflow in English, Hindi, and Bengali.) Tj
T*
(3. Combine questionnaire scoring with text, audio, image, and passive signals.) Tj
T*
(4. Offer live preview before saving.) Tj
T*
(5. Keep the dashboard usable when backend connectivity is weak or unavailable.) Tj
T*
(6. Persist assessment records for later retrieval.) Tj
T*
(7. Provide PDF exports for records and quality checks.) Tj
T*
(8. Support research publication, ablation studies, and future clinical validation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Main Components) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.1 Frontend Dashboard) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Files:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- web/index.html \(/c:/Rural%20Mental%20Heath%20Screening%20AI/web/index.html\)) Tj
T*
(- web/app.js \(/c:/Rural%20Mental%20Heath%20Screening%20AI/web/app.js\)) Tj
T*
(- web/styles.css \(/c:/Rural%20Mental%20Heath%20Screening%20AI/web/styles.css\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
