(Before saving, the dashboard can generate a preview from the current browser inputs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This preview is used to:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- show the likely screening outcome,) Tj
T*
(- display NLP and safety insights,) Tj
T*
(- show modality readiness,) Tj
T*
(- help the user identify missing inputs,) Tj
T*
(- keep the user aware of whether the backend is available.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If the backend is unavailable, the app falls back to offline heuristics and clearly labels the result.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3 Adaptive Test) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The adaptive test asks one question at a time.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Working behavior:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- it loads the first question,) Tj
T*
(- collects the answer,) Tj
T*
(- chooses the next question based on the previous response state,) Tj
T*
(- continues until the adaptive session is complete,) Tj
T*
(- then saves the final record.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This reduces the number of unnecessary questions and makes the screening flow more field-friendly.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.4 Analytics Hub) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The analytics hub is the detail view for one selected assessment.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It shows:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- the final combined result,) Tj
T*
(- the questionnaire score breakdown,) Tj
T*
(- component contribution from text, audio, image, and passive signals,) Tj
T*
(- modality quality and availability,) Tj
T*
(- NLP and safety signals,) Tj
T*
(- recommendation and disclaimer,) Tj
T*
(- model statistics,) Tj
T*
(- quality check summary,) Tj
T*
(- trajectory and trend summary,) Tj
T*
(- feature snapshots and record details.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The analytics page is intentionally more verbose than the assessment workspace because it is meant for review and analysis.) Tj
ET
