(### 4.5 Records and Reports) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The records panel is used to:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- search and fetch records by assessment ID,) Tj
T*
(- inspect selected assessment details,) Tj
T*
(- export PDF reports,) Tj
T*
(- delete a record,) Tj
T*
(- hide a report from the visible panel.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important visibility rules:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- demo/backend records are hidden from the normal user list,) Tj
T*
(- hidden report entries are removed from the visible Records and Reports panel,) Tj
T*
(- only visible user records are used in the main record list,) Tj
T*
(- demo records are excluded from PDF export.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. Data Flow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system uses this overall flow:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. User starts a session in the browser.) Tj
T*
(2. Frontend builds a payload from profile, questionnaire, narrative, and optional media inputs.) Tj
T*
(3. Payload is sent to /api/preview or /api/assessments.) Tj
T*
(4. Backend validates the input.) Tj
T*
(5. Feature extraction and scoring produce modality and overall outputs.) Tj
T*
(6. The record is saved in storage.) Tj
T*
(7. The frontend refreshes the result list and detail panels.) Tj
T*
(8. The user can fetch, review, export, delete, or hide the record later.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If the backend cannot be reached:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- the dashboard can still render a limited preview,) Tj
T*
(- the assessment can be stored locally,) Tj
T*
(- the app queues it for later sync,) Tj
T*
(- the UI clearly marks the offline state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 6. API Reference) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The backend exposes these routes:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- GET / - dashboard shell) Tj
T*
(- GET /health - health check) Tj
ET
