(## 16. Deployment and Setup) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Typical setup:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python -m venv .venv) Tj
T*
(.\\.venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1) Tj
T*
(pip install -r requirements.txt) Tj
T*
(python dashboard_server.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Then open:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(http://127.0.0.1:8000/) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 17. Operational Notes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Before using this project in a real setting:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- verify consent workflows,) Tj
T*
(- confirm privacy and data-handling policy,) Tj
T*
(- test offline recovery,) Tj
T*
(- confirm PDF export behavior,) Tj
T*
(- test the hidden-report and delete-record actions,) Tj
T*
(- check model bundle availability,) Tj
T*
(- make sure sample data is not mistaken for real patient data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 18. Current Working Behavior Summary) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(At runtime, the system now behaves as follows:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- text and image are treated as usable when they carry actual signal or metadata,) Tj
T*
(- recommendations adapt to risk level and language,) Tj
T*
(- model statistics and NLP summaries avoid empty placeholder states when data is available,) Tj
T*
(- demo records stay hidden from the user-facing list,) Tj
T*
(- reports can be hidden from the visible panel without deleting the underlying record,) Tj
T*
(- the dashboard can fall back to offline preview when necessary,) Tj
T*
(- the research paper package and documentation are included in-repo.) Tj
ET
